{
  "text": "To call domains we used heatmaps binned at 40 kb resolution. Dixon TADs were obtained using algorithm described in (2) with default parameters. Armatus TADs were obtained using algorithm described in [CITATION_1] . Size of domains obtained using this algorithm depends on parameter γ (59). Indeed, we observed several sets of domains corresponding to different γ values). We summarize results obtained with different γ values in a set of 'consensus domains', as described in [CITATION_2] . TADtree TADs were obtained using an algorithm described in (60) with parameters S = 50, M = 25.",
